HW 3 - Bicubic Bezier Patches

This program, evaluates a 3D bi-cubic Bezier patch and approximates it with triangles.

# Calculation of Normal
The code that implements the surface normal calculations can be found inside CG_hw3 between lines 60-92

# Specifications
  - The program is written in Python on Mac and the main executable file is name CG_hw3

# Execution

      Run the Makefile to create the executable and then run the following command:
      ./CG_hw3 -f filename -u num_u -v num_v -r radius -F > out.iv